<br />
i walk first so the sites are less important.    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ent-pipeweed/ uruk sitecontrol<br />
<br />
First, this deck seems ugly but it was a big metachoice. <br />
Fellowship:<br />
Scared of burdens and sauron grind I thought it to be wise to come with a lot of burden-removal and healings.<br />
Thus the pipeweed-ent combination was born. Gandalf was my main character. Being able to discard all conditions and remove those pesty possessions, the opposites shadow stands little chance. Disruption is cool. Then of course I put in gandalfs pipe 3 times for the burden removal.<br />
Isildus with gorns pipe (3 times) was the best idea ever. 2 times 4 pipeweeds and the pipes are unstoppable. <br />
The ents are also very handy. With an average 4 vitality they are not easily destroyed :P. And when they are: play another. They also cycle like mad. use sent back to deicard gandalf in times of need.Treebeard takes back ‘sent back’ in the regroup and then play a Gandalf from hand. A cool combo. <br />
Shadow:<br />
Just 3 things:<br />
1.	I go first. (bid high) so I control the sites before my opponent does.<br />
2.	Sarumans power<br />
3.	Sarumans power<br />
Of course burning of the westfold is better and pillage of rohan is cool but the main reason is to disrupt. So : control one site?&#61664; sarumans power.<br />
<br />
Of course feel free to adapt.<br />
All of these rares I own only one time. So I suggest a little servant to the s/f-twist and of course lindenroot instead of another forest guardian. Maybe the best change is to put in saved from the fire...<br />
<br />
This deck worked for me, I hope you like the idea.<br />
<br />
